'''ISKCON Leicester''' is a [[Hindu temple]] in [[Leicester]] run by the [[International Society for Krishna Consciousness]].<ref name="bbc36935851">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-leicestershire-36935851|title=Exploded Iskcon Temple in Leicester is replaced|last=|first=|date=31 July 2016|website=BBC News|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-02}}</ref> It occupies a [[Grade II* listed]] building in Granby Street in the centre of Leicester. The building was originally constructed in 1872-74 as a bank branch for [[Leicestershire Bank]], now part of [[HSBC]].<ref name=leicestermercury/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://historicengland.org.uk/listing/the-list/list-entry/1074047|title=HSBC, 31, GRANBY STREET|last=|first=|date=|website=Historic England|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-02}}</ref>

The temple replaces an earlier temple in Thoresby Street in [[North Evington]] which was damaged in 2010 by a gas explosion.<ref name=bbc36935851/><ref name=leicestermercury>{{Cite web|url=http://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/hindu-temple-plan-hsbc-bank-leicester/story-19715970-detail/story.html|title=Hindu temple plan for former HSBC bank|last=|first=|date=2013-08-28|website=Leicester Mercury|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-leicestershire-16218585|title=Leicester Hare Krishna temple moves to ex Midland Bank|last=|first=|date=16 December 2011|website=BBC News|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-02}}</ref>

