'''Inwangsa''' is a [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] [[temple]] of the [[Bonwon Order]] in Mt. [[Inwangsan]], [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]. It is located at San 2 [[Muak-dong]], in the [[Jongno-gu]] area of the city. When [[Taejo of Joseon|King Taejo]] of [[Joseon Dynasty]] established the capital city in Seoul, he assigned Josaeng (조생 祖生), a monk from a Buddhist temple affiliated to the royal court as the head monk of the new temple to establish it at the site.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatemple.net/korea_temple/traditional_temple/history/view.asp?temple_seq=2569&category_id=7 |title=The history of the foundation |publisher=Koreatemple.net |language=Korean |accessdate=2008-05-05}}</ref>

